casts.text:
Liquidation cascade.

User A is long with a Liquidation price at $118k. User B is long with a liquidation at $115k. User C is long with liquidation at $110k.  

The order book may thin, as well, because it's friday or a holiday or whatever so as limit buys get filled, they don't get replaced.

$118k is hit and user A is liquidated dropping price to $115k where user B gets liquidated. There isn't enough time for market makers to put in bids so price falls to $110k where user C is liquidated...

Finally some market maker or whale decides the liquidation cascade/forced selling is exhausted enough that they can step in and buy for a quick gain on the rebound, and, hopefully, price stabilizes
